# Research Article Demonstration Document

## Steps involved in the setup

### Google Document setup

1. Connect Zotero  
2. Set Citation Style: CMOS Author Date  
3. Test citation addition   
4. Change Zotero language, Citation style   
5. Add standard layout parts

## Publishing from Google Docs

### Option 1: Output to use Paged Media CSS and Vivliostyle

Zotero linked version \- HTML

1. Save document as HTML  
2. Upload online \- in this case GitHub  
3. Read document in Vivliostyle  
   1. As A4 \- no style \- Viewer only   
      1. [GDoc](https://vivliostyle.org/viewer/#src=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mrchristian/gdocs/refs/heads/main/Researcharticledemo.html&f=epubcfi\(/2!/4/54\)&style=data:,/*%3Cviewer%3E*/%0A@page%20%7B%20size:%20a4;%20%7D%0A/*%3C/viewer%3E*/&spread=false)

      1. F \= G \* m1 \* m2 / d2 1

Newton's Law of Gravity states that attractive force (gravity) exists between any two objects.

* F: Gravitational Force, in N  
* m1: Mass of Object 1, in Kg  
* m2: Mass of Object 2, in Kg  
* d: Distance between the two Objects, in m  
* G: Gravitation Constant, is 6.67 × 10-11 N.m2/kg2
